main event: A bright white object was observed entering the atmosphere at 21.56N/158.20W in the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The object was observed by an Aloha Airlines aircraft at 05:16Z on February 25, 1963.
The object was traveling at a high speed and burned out 30 degrees above the horizon.
The sighting was confirmed by a second Aloha Airlines aircraft.
The object was tracked on ground-based radar for 3 minutes.
The Air Force did not provide an evaluation of the sighting.
